text:
When using the modified selector with a FileSet, the call to saveCache() fails if a single file has been modified.  The result is that the cache is not updated and the file is improperly re-selected on subsequent calls.

Here is the existing code in org.apache.tools.ant.types.selectors.modifiedselectorModifiedSelector.java:

   /**
    * save the cache file
    */
    protected void saveCache() {
        if (getModified() > 1) {
            cache.save();
            setModified(0);
        }
    }

It should probably be rewritten as:

   /**
    * save the cache file
    */
    protected void saveCache() {
        if (getModified() > 0) {
            cache.save();
            setModified(0);
        }
    }
